		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>The Scarblade is a dark and rugged bastard sword forged from a chaos shard. It resonates with greater power when it is within the Chaos Scar.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Weapon</b><b>:</b> Heavy blade</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +2d10 critical damage, or +3d10 when within the Chaos Scar.</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Properties:</b>\n<ul>\n<li>Once per turn, when you hit with an attack using this weapon, the creature you hit takes 1d6 extra fire damage.</li>\n<li>Wounds created by the Scarblade leave ragged, ashen scars even when healed by magic. The weapon emits red sparks and leaves a black scorch mark when it hits.</li>\n</ul></p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power âœ¦ Daily (Standard Action)</b></p><p>Striking the ground with the sword creates a crevasse 1square wide, 5 squares long, and up to 2 squares deep beginning in the square you strike and extending in a straight line away from you. Any creature that is entirely in the affected area must save or fall into the crevasse.</p>",
